msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModule.cmake:443
msgid ""
"Modules and groups are enable and disable preferences are specified using a "
"5-way flag setting:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModule.cmake:446
msgid "``YES``: The module or group must be built."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModule.cmake:447
msgid "``NO``: The module or group must not be built."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModule.cmake:448
msgid "``WANT``: The module or group should be built if possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModule.cmake:449
msgid ""
"``DONT_WANT``: The module or group should only be built if required (e.g., "
"via a dependency)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModule.cmake:451
msgid ""
"``DEFAULT``: Acts as either ``WANT`` or ``DONT_WANT`` based on the group "
"settings for the module or ``WANT_BY_DEFAULT`` option to :cmake:command:"
"`vtk_module_scan` if no other preference is specified. This is usually "
"handled via another setting in the main project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModule.cmake:456
msgid ""
"If a ``YES`` module preference requires a module with a ``NO`` preference, "
"an error is raised."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModule.cmake:459
msgid ""
"A module with a setting of ``DEFAULT`` will look for its first non-"
"``DEFAULT`` group setting and only if all of those are set to ``DEFAULT`` is "
"the ``WANT_BY_DEFAULT`` setting used."
msgstr ""

